@startuml
title POST /api/v1/registration/accounts — OAUTH (201 Created)
autonumber

actor Client
participant "register_account()\n_register_oauth()" as View
participant "RegistrationOAuth\nSerializer" as Serializer
participant "_google_userinfo()" as Google
participant "validate_registration\n_code()" as Validate
participant "redeem_non_student\n_oauth_invite()" as Redeem
participant "create_user_from\n_payload()" as CreateUser
database Postgres
entity "Google OAuth API" as GoogleAPI

Client -> View: POST /registration/accounts\n{method: "OAUTH", code,\naccessToken, firstName, lastName}
View -> Serializer: is_valid(raise_exception=True)
Serializer --> View: validated data

View -> Google: _google_userinfo(accessToken)
Google -> GoogleAPI: GET googleapis.com/oauth2/v3/userinfo\nAuthorization: Bearer {token}
GoogleAPI --> Google: {sub, email, email_verified,\nname, picture}
Google --> View: google profile data
View -> View: extract google_subject, google_email\nvalidate both present

== @transaction.atomic ==

View -> Redeem: redeem_non_student_oauth_invite(\ncode, subject, email, names, verified, picture)

Redeem -> Postgres: SELECT registration_codes\nWHERE code_hash = ? FOR UPDATE
Postgres --> Redeem: RegistrationCode (locked)
Redeem -> Redeem: validate code_type != STUDENT

Redeem -> Postgres: SELECT EXISTS oauth_accounts\nWHERE provider=GOOGLE\nAND subject = ?
Postgres --> Redeem: False (not linked)

Redeem -> Postgres: SELECT EXISTS app_users\nWHERE username = email OR email = email
Postgres --> Redeem: False (email not taken)

Redeem -> Redeem: generate_managed_username()
Redeem -> Postgres: SELECT EXISTS app_users\nWHERE username = ?
Postgres --> Redeem: False (unique)

Redeem -> CreateUser: create_user_from_payload(\nrole=TEACHER, creator=None, password=None)
CreateUser -> Postgres: INSERT INTO app_users\n(username, name, email, password=unusable)
CreateUser -> Postgres: DELETE FROM user_roles WHERE user_id = ?
CreateUser -> Postgres: INSERT INTO user_roles
CreateUser -> Postgres: INSERT INTO teacher_profiles
CreateUser --> Redeem: User

Redeem -> Postgres: INSERT/UPDATE oauth_accounts\n(provider=GOOGLE, subject, user, email)
Redeem -> Postgres: UPDATE oauth_accounts\nSET email_verified, picture_url, last_login_at

Redeem -> Postgres: UPDATE registration_codes\nSET times_used += 1
Redeem --> View: User

== end transaction ==

View -> View: RefreshToken.for_user(user)\ngenerate JWT tokens
View -> View: build_user_response(user, tokens)

View --> Client: 201 Created\n{message, username, name, email,\naccessToken, refreshToken,\nrole, courseId: null}
@enduml
